<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-548-016  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 548 016.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  August 21 1989 v6 n33 p47(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multimedia integraton from Apple: few bite. (Apple promotesmultimedia integration at Macworld Expo)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grygo, Gene.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Apple pushed Macintosh-based multimedia applications heavily atthe 1989 Macworld Expo, but industry observers expect the marketto be slow to embrace the new technology.andP;  Company officialsdemonstrated videodisc, CD, videotape, and other interfaces whileApple Pres John Sculley emphasized HyperCard multimedia productsin his keynote address.andP;  ABC News, Newsweek, Harvard University,and divisions of Warner Communications and McGraw-Hill InformationServices are offering Mac-based multimedia educational tools.andO;Analysts say Apple is promoting the new integration because it iswell-suited for the Macintosh, but note that the market awaits a'killer application' and the proliferation of fiber-optic networksbefore other manufacturers are likely to give multimedia thesupport it needs to become viable.andP;  Apple is working to define itsMedia Control Architecture as a standard multimedia interface.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (usage).andO;Topic:     Multimedia TechnologyMarket PenetrationComputer Systems IntegrationApplicationsMacWorld Exposition.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Multimedia Integration From Apple: Few BiteandM;BOSTON -- Apple Computer was in hard-sell mode at the Macworld expositionearlier this month concerning the multimedia integration of its Macintoshes.andM;Nonetheless, industry watchers said the market will be slow to embrace thespecial integration of varied media.andM;Undaunted, Apple officials demonstrated Macs with videodisc players, CD-audioplayers, videotape recorders and similar devices.andM;&quot;We believe that everyone who owns a Mac will want [multimedia integration],&quot;said Albert Chu, a marketing manager for Apple's information products.andP;  Chusaid he also envisions broad-based office applications such as theintegration of voice mail with spreadsheets.andP;  For now, Apple has to &quot;seedsoftware developers,&quot; he said.andM;Cupertino, Calif.-based Apple has been pushing the new integration because itis well-suited for Macs, said Benny Lorenzo, a senior technology analyst withVolpe, Covington and Welty, an investment bank in San Francisco.andP;  Apple wouldlike multimedia integration to take off like desktop publishing has, Lorenzosaid.andM;&quot;It's a market that Apple has been trying to participate in,&quot; he said.andP;  But,he added, the market needs to be nudged along with the help of softwaredevelopers and support from other hardware manufacturers.andP;  Other than Apple,only IBM has shown an interest in the market for multimedia integration, hesaid.andM;&quot;The question is, how big a market is it and how big a market is it likely tobe?&quot;andP;  Lorenzo said.andM;Among the conditions necessary for integration to take off is a &quot;killerapplication&quot; and the proliferation of fiber-optic networks, Lorenzo said.andO;Apple also has to educate the industry about the advantages of theintegration possibilities.andM;During his keynote speech at Macworld, John Sculley, Apple's president, spentmost of his time showing off the latest &quot;information products&quot; usingHyperCard, the HyperCard CD-Audio Toolkit and the HyperCard VideodiscToolkit.andM;The first crop of products are educational tools from ABC News, Newsweek andHarvard University as well as from divisions of Warner Communications andMcGraw-Hill Information Services.andP;  Boston-based public television stationWGBH has also announced a Mac-based product.andM;The products demonstrated included interactive videodisc documentaries on theconflcts of the Middle East and on animal behavior, and a graphics programthat accompanies a Mozart opera on a CD.andP;  There was also a CD-ROM-basedresource of information on Macintosh-related products.andM;Beyond these initial endorsements, Apple officials also announced that theywould be working with developers to define the Apple Media ControlArchitecture to provide a consistent standard interface.andM;At the moment, software developers have to write a customized interface foreach media device, the officials said.andP;  The new architecture will provide acore interface code to media devices that developers can adapt to thefunctions of their products.andO;</TEXT></DOC>